Charging an electric car when you live in a flat is — let's be honest — significantly harder than if you have your own driveway. But it's absolutely not impossible, and it's getting easier every year.

Whether you own a flat, rent an apartment, or live in a block with shared parking, there are real solutions available right now. The key is knowing your rights, understanding the grants available, and choosing the right hardware for your situation.

This guide covers everything: the best chargers for multi-occupancy buildings, leaseholder rights, the OZEV grant for flats and renters, and what to do if installing a charger genuinely isn't an option.

